President Donald Trump has announced that he will continue the national emergency declared on September 14, 2001, in response to the terrorist attacks of September 11, 2001. This national emergency, which grants the President certain powers and authorities, will be extended for another year due to the continuing terrorist threat against the United States. The announcement was made in accordance with section 202(d) of the National Emergencies Act. The notice will be published in the Federal Register and transmitted to Congress.